The paper proposes a neural network framework for reconstructing the 3D mesh of a human body from multi-view images, which involves computer vision (CV) and graphics (GR) techniques. The use of multi-view images also suggests the involvement of multimedia (MM) techniques. The paper also mentions the use of synthetic data and validation, which suggests the involvement of machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.GR, and cs.MM, followed by cs.LG and cs.AI.
